cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.SOC, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on social groups in social media platforms and uses community detection algorithms to extract user-defined groups. It also applies sociological theories to classify groups into topical or social categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). The paper also involves data analysis and machine learning techniques to predict group labels, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the evolution and activity of social groups, which could be relevant to cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences).
